Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.60,0:00:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain rises on a mysterious new era...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.47,0:00:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Monday 7:00 reasoning show.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.35,0:00:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A puzzling code written in her grandfather's diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.60,0:00:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yamaguchi prefecture is the stage for a treasure hunt!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.77,0:00:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.27,0:00:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.76,0:02:00.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is all, you see, dedicated to Yoshida Shouin...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:04.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The man who trained the people that would become\Nthe leaders behind the Meiji Restoration.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.52,0:02:07.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The great teacher has been enshrined in this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.38,0:02:08.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Shouin?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.61,0:02:11.96,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He lived 150 years ago, during the last\Nyears of the shogunate (bakumatsu).
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.06,0:02:13.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The Meiji "mishin"? (sewing machine)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.89,0:02:16.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Not "mishin" (sewing machine), the Meiji "isshin" (restoration).\N(Meiji is a common sewing machine brand in Japan.)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:22.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouin was a studious man who broadened his\Nknowledge by traveling throughout Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.15,0:02:25.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he wanted to change the country,\Nhe studied foreign works as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.99,0:02:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when Japan excluded foreigners.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.07,0:02:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He poured his heart into studying western culture...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.78,0:02:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the risk of his life, he even tried to stowaway to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.50,0:02:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before his plans had come to fruition...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.80,0:02:40.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: Shouin's final words, "Even if my body shall, in this\NMusashi field, rot away, I will at least retain the spirit of Yamato."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.83,0:02:40.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouin was executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.50,0:02:44.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, Shouin's intentions were adopted by others.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.51,0:02:48.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the pupils who listened to his\Nteachings went on to change society.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.22,0:02:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you get all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.76,0:02:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did we have to bring a bunch of brats\Nalong for our Japanese history homework?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon, it's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.19,0:03:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having to come along is a real nuisance for us too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.40,0:03:04.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was my line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.32,0:03:07.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.53,0:03:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hand it over!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.20,0:03:10.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.62,0:03:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.12,0:03:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.37,0:03:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.84,0:03:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.47,0:03:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're being threatened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.39,0:03:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.27,0:03:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said if I didn't hand over this diary,\Nsomething horrible would happen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.69,0:03:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that if I told the police, he couldn't guarantee my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.27,0:03:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he told me several times over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea who it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.20,0:03:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This diary is a little worn-out, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.94,0:03:57.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My late grandpa left it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.38,0:04:01.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(210,0)}Kobayakawa Kimiko (21)\NCollege Student
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:04:01.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But the contents are just some puzzles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.96,0:04:03.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Puzzles?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.21,0:04:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandpa loved word games.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.46,0:04:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would always be writing down puzzles in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.13,0:04:14.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, before he could write out all the solutions, my grandpa...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.26,0:04:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five years ago today, he passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My grandpa was really fond of Master Shouin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.31,0:04:25.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I went to visit the Shouin shrine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.19,0:04:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would that guy be after something like this diary?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.11,0:04:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.53,0:04:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, could I possibly ask you to investigate?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.91,0:04:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand. I'd be happy to accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.83,0:04:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.04,0:04:45.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? There's something stuck inside where it was torn earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.42,0:04:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.00,0:04:49.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"November 30th...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.26,0:04:52.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Only by the twilight will the true treasure be illuminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.97,0:04:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Solve the puzzle of the fox."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.55,0:04:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.14,0:05:00.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Do you have any idea what this is about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Treasure? That reminds me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.23,0:05:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko, I have a magnificent treasure\Nthat could buy the whole country.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.69,0:05:12.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wh-What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.95,0:05:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A treasure that could buy the country!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:17.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many bowls of eel over rice (unajuu) would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:20.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would anyone know the conversion rate to unajuu?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.54,0:05:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what could "The puzzle of the fox" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.17,0:05:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.04,0:05:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a picture of a fox here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.59,0:05:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Feed the carp to the fox." What could that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A moat with carp. That might possibly refer\Nto a scenic spot that's near my family home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:40.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is your family home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.22,0:05:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Tsuwano in Shimane prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.89,0:05:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we need to go to your family home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.06,0:05:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We do?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.11,0:05:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,November 30th is tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.15,0:05:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't miss this chance! We leave first thing in the morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.40,0:05:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But can we get a ticket now for tomorrow morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.24,0:05:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.87,0:06:03.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leave that task to Suzuki Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.25,0:06:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I use my family's connections...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.58,0:06:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter if it's the bullet train (shinkansen) or an express sleeper...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.25,0:06:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.29,0:06:12.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's to be expected from the daughter of Suzuki Financial.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.13,0:06:12.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.09,0:06:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the great detective Mouri Kogorou on the job,\Nthat treasure will be discovered before dinnertime!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.39,0:06:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's been a complication.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.43,0:06:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's woman's gone to see the detective, Mouri Kogorou.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.73,0:06:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, I understand. Keep on watching her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.91,0:06:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really have to thank you for undertaking this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.87,0:06:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.08,0:06:48.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth could this stand for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.92,0:06:51.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Feed the carp to the fox."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.29,0:06:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do carp taste good?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.92,0:06:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you guys doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.97,0:06:57.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're doing what we can for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.47,0:07:00.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, we were the ones Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}\Nasked for help from in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.01,0:07:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.51,0:07:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That diary of puzzles...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.77,0:07:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your grandpa must have been a really fun person, Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.89,0:07:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was always coming up with interesting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.50,0:07:19.90,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Kimiko, if you were going to send a letter to the\Nfuture, how much postage would you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.87,0:07:18.91,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(250,250)}Kobayakawa Shigetoshi\NKimiko's Grandpa
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.66,0:07:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A letter to the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.41,0:07:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it? What was the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.20,0:07:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.59,0:07:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin-Yamaguchi! Shin-Yamaguchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.26,0:07:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To reach Tsuwano from here, we\Nneed to transfer to the Yamaguchi line.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.26,0:07:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.31,0:07:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.14,0:07:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.64,0:07:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.60,0:07:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kawaguchi Shigeru, I'm a pal of Kimiko's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.40,0:07:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard that Kimiko had a close call while in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.82,0:07:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're the ones who protected Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.78,0:08:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, for we are...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.66,0:08:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Detective Boys!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.76,0:08:07.68,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:10.51,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}Kawaguchi Shigeru (21)\NKimiko's Friend
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.31,0:08:10.30,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As her friend, thanks from me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.50,0:08:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Kimiko, are you heading back to Tsuwano from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.09,0:08:19.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.51,0:08:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's me. Nine tickets will be\Nenough. Cancel the rest for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.69,0:08:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.94,0:08:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gotten hot coming here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.19,0:08:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It smells really awesome too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.28,0:08:40.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hurry up and get on!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.70,0:08:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.37,0:08:54.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're only running this steam locomotive for a limited time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.92,0:08:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really full. It must be hard to get tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.96,0:09:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, if you have connections, it's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.72,0:09:05.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a hot spring here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.47,0:09:07.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want a hot spring, the Yuda onsen is popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.35,0:09:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person said his name was Kawaguchi Shigeru, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.98,0:09:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cellphone strap matches that guy's pendant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.27,0:09:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are initials on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.86,0:09:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s has "K.K." for "Kobayakawa Kimiko"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.57,0:09:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person had "A.T." But if his name is Kawaguchi\NShigeru, it should be "S.K.", shouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.66,0:09:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would he be trying to hide his real name?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.62,0:09:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, if you have connections, it's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.29,0:09:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I use my family's connections...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.63,0:09:40.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter if it's the bullet train (shinkansen) or an express sleeper...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be a piece of cake!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.92,0:09:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means he has a connection who\Nis an influential person in this area
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.61,0:10:01.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck are you intending?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.57,0:10:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.45,0:10:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought this was the way to the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.03,0:10:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.33,0:10:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.29,0:10:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tsuwano! Tsuwano!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.71,0:10:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Might you be Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.55,0:10:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.27,0:10:28.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.31,0:10:32.35,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(210,0)}Kikkawa Tsuneo (60)\N{\fs10}Kobayakawa Family Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.76,0:10:32.36,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I work for the Kobayakawa family. My name is Kikkawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.81,0:10:35.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to put you to any bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.06,0:10:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the daughter of the house with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.40,0:10:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? She was just here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.73,0:10:41.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no! Could she have been kidnapped!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.90,0:10:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.57,0:10:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot to buy a souvenir for my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:47.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I just bought this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.66,0:10:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.61,0:10:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I go all the way to Tokyo and I buy a souvenir here, isn't that funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.29,0:10:56.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to your friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.96,0:10:58.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he already left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.79,0:11:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.01,0:11:07.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Development is our home town's future!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.65,0:11:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone is already aware\Nof my past record.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.67,0:11:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.68,0:11:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name's Takahashi Hisamichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.68,0:11:18.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's involved in real estate and construction\Nalong the hub of the San'in region (SW Honshu).
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.27,0:11:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He has an extensive business developing resorts and such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.15,0:11:25.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now he's announcing his candidacy as\Na member of the prefectural assembly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.03,0:11:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this area will be invigorated and everyone's lives will be enriched.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who can do it is me, Takahashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.83,0:11:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And only me, Takahashi Hisamichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.20,0:11:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} makes me feel reassured.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.46,0:11:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who loves this town the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.63,0:11:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think such a splendid father could have a son like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.13,0:11:50.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Atsushi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, eh? How long will he keep acting like a delinquent?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:54.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Tonomachi street.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.89,0:11:58.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is where old-time samurai houses are still standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.77,0:12:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! What huge carp!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:05.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the old days, they were raised for emergency food.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.15,0:12:09.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the fox going to eat all of these carp?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.40,0:12:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? This is a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.28,0:12:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not supposed to think he will really eat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.99,0:12:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for taking the trip here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.25,0:12:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. I'm just happy your daughter is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.00,0:12:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing is, recently we just had a thief break into this house too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.80,0:12:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could they have been after the diary?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.89,0:12:39.64,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,0)}Kobayakawa Hideko (48)\NKimiko's Mother
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:34.25,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That might be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.52,0:12:39.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please, find the culprit any way you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.10,0:12:41.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.14,0:12:46.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said she had heard something\Nabout a treasure from her grandpa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.82,0:12:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard things about a treasure too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.11,0:12:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After the war, the Kobayakawa house was the first\Nto be rebuilt, supposedly thanks to the treasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.33,0:13:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I know how much effort my father put into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.17,0:13:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I know it wasn't thanks to any treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.88,0:13:11.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there are a lot of people who don't think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.05,0:13:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially some people who rose to power\Nin the turmoil after the Second World War.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.47,0:13:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since historically we've been deeply trusted by the local people,\Nthey've been hostile to the Kobayakawa family at every opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.56,0:13:27.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, those people might be the ones after the diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.07,0:13:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't let the bad guys find the treasure before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.03,0:13:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.07,0:13:34.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, can I eat this now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.99,0:13:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, please go ahead and eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.08,0:13:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:42.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These rice-powder sweets are a Yamaguchi specialty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.91,0:13:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're a little different than the ones\Nfrom Nagoya, you can wiggle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.50,0:13:50.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.46,0:13:51.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wiggly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.71,0:13:53.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mine's already gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:14:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eating the carp means the carp would disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.64,0:14:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko, can I borrow your copy of this page?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.54,0:14:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.69,0:14:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.49,0:14:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.28,0:14:19.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The carp have disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.78,0:14:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.75,0:14:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure that "Feed the carp to the fox" meant this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.00,0:14:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? All you did was fold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.50,0:14:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! There are characters at the fold.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.01,0:14:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.17,0:14:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Characters appeared when the ends\Nof the canal were joined together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.93,0:14:41.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Below the top of the hidden Inari."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.72,0:14:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it says "Inari", the Taikodani Inari shrine is in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:49.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! The treasure is at the Taikodani Inari shrine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.65,0:14:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.66,0:15:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a mind-bogglingly large number of Torii arches here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.66,0:15:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they say there are around 1000 of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.66,0:15:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,1,000!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.58,0:15:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to climb this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.25,0:15:13.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what it looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.09,0:15:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.09,0:15:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.97,0:15:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a bit further.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.06,0:15:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a long way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.68,0:15:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So lift up your leg!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.15,0:15:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:36.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.12,0:15:38.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is a terrific view, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.53,0:15:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, what does "Below the top of the hidden Inari" mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.37,0:15:45.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.58,0:15:46.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it food?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.64,0:15:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fried tofu?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.96,0:15:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not for eating, it's an offering.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.17,0:15:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fried tofu is the Great Fox's favorite food.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.21,0:15:57.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, say, say, what do they do with the offerings?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.92,0:15:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you thinking about stealing them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.76,0:16:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The gods will punish you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.55,0:16:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.64,0:16:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The offerings are made at the main shrine over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.56,0:16:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or at the shrine in the back, either one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.52,0:16:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that maybe be it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That "Hidden Inari"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.32,0:16:19.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.11,0:16:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't seem there's anything here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.03,0:16:25.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's fried tofu in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.41,0:16:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way you can't steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.91,0:16:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, I'm not going to take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.96,0:16:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.37,0:16:33.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.63,0:16:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a whole lot of foxes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.38,0:16:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There really are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.13,0:16:39.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.09,0:16:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got it! That "Hidden Inari" is referring to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.30,0:16:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not there. Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.18,0:16:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The "Hidden Inari" is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we just have "Below the top" remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.57,0:16:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're using a stone to signify fried tofu.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.07,0:17:01.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Fried tofu?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ue" (top) as kanji can be read "a-ge" (up, but also fried tofu).
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.28,0:17:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore the treasure is under that stone fried tofu!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.66,0:17:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so smart!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.33,0:17:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awesome, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.83,0:17:16.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.00,0:17:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.13,0:17:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.05,0:17:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see. There's some kind of paper in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.14,0:17:28.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.01,0:17:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a map, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something's written at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.10,0:17:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.81,0:17:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Reflect the castle in the eye of the cat and look under the mouse."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.32,0:17:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cat, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.36,0:17:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.03,0:17:48.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hole looks like it was made on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.66,0:17:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no page with a picture of a mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.12,0:17:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another code?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.50,0:17:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This looks like it was drawn based on an old map of Hagi city.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.55,0:18:02.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hagi? That's in Yamaguchi prefecture, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.63,0:18:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and it's related to the person\Nthat my grandpa liked, Master Shouin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.43,0:18:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it. So the treasure's in Hagi then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.56,0:18:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So they're going to Hagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.89,0:18:18.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't lose them! Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.74,0:18:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.91,0:18:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.66,0:18:40.79,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,For some reason this really looks like an old town.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:44.14,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,In Hagi, the old-time street patterns still remain today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.55,0:18:47.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, if you're looking at a map from the Edo period...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.26,0:18:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could walk through the town now and still find your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.60,0:18:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we're seeing the same street fronts as the\Npatriots from the Meiji Restoration then, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.35,0:18:59.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, this was the birthplace of the Meiji Restoration.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.65,0:19:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There it is again, the Meiji sewing machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.07,0:19:03.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Meiji Restoration.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.28,0:19:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the reform that gave Japan its chance\Nto become a modern country like it is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.32,0:19:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lot of the people who accomplished the Meiji.\NRestoration were from this town of Hagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.92,0:19:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nekonocho? (Cat St.)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.42,0:19:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this have something to do with that code?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.67,0:19:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hagi has roughly 250 streets with names like that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.18,0:19:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here in the old days, among the retainers of Mouri Terumoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.60,0:19:38.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some people who really loved cats lived\Nhere, so they called it Nekonocho.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.23,0:19:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A real cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.86,0:19:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cat? That's it, I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.86,0:19:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've solved the code?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.32,0:19:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.49,0:19:53.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shiro" didn't mean a castle (shiro); it meant a white (shiroi) wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.83,0:19:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, somewhere near this white\Nplaster wall where we can see this cat sitting...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.87,0:20:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the hidden treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.04,0:20:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, exactly like now, that cat...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.21,0:20:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, kitty!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.55,0:20:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's completely wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.30,0:20:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're having a joke on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.51,0:20:14.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm worried that it wasn't a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.10,0:20:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the guy who called himself Kawaguchi Shigeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.49,0:20:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear what I told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.86,0:20:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.57,0:20:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.24,0:20:37.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That man?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.79,0:20:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the man who attacked Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.85,0:20:48.14,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is the house where the doctor, Aoki\NShuusuke, lived during the Edo period.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.92,0:20:51.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've heard that a treasure was found here a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.51,0:20:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're very familiar with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.43,0:20:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there really a treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.22,0:20:58.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, there was gold buried in the cellar.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.68,0:21:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Buried gold!?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.69,0:21:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There definitely must be a treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.60,0:21:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.98,0:21:06.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm getting all excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.36,0:21:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.94,0:21:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we go see the remains of the Hagi castle next?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.91,0:21:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the relationship between Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and those men?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.37,0:21:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who is Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for real?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.50,0:21:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and get in! Settle down!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.05,0:21:33.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You there! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.43,0:21:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.89,0:21:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer! Hurry, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.51,0:21:41.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quick, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.98,0:21:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.98,0:21:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.90,0:21:47.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm borrowing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.74,0:21:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not getting away!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.16,0:22:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.12,0:22:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't think those guys would go this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.21,0:22:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't paying enough attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.71,0:22:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could there really be treasure big enough to buy the country?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.05,0:22:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And those men who are after it, who the hell are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.35,0:22:22.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that voice from that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.89,0:22:24.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer! Hurry, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.56,0:22:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that voice was...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.87,0:24:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.92,0:24:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,CAT\N(neko)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.07,0:24:30.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look forward to the next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.30,0:24:27.24,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Meow! Next time we find the treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.25,0:24:28.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I can eat lots of unajuu, meow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.79,0:24:29.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's meow-meow stupid.
